cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.CE, cs.VE 

Reasoning: 

- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper presents a behavioral compact model for 3D NAND flash memory, which is an emerging technology in the field of memory devices. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the different parasitic capacitance coupling effects applicable to the 3D geometry of the vertical channel Macaroni body charge-trap flash memory, which is related to the architecture of the memory device. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper mentions the parasitic capacitance coupling effects, which are related to the electromagnetic behavior of the memory device. 
- cs.CE (Circuit Design): The paper presents a compact model that would equip the circuit designers with an effective tool for design-exploration of 3D NAND flash memory devices. 
- cs.VE (Verification and Validation): The paper discusses the model parameter extraction methodology, which is related to the verification and validation of the model.
